<!DOCTYPE html><html><head><title>$ command line ruby cheat sheets</title><link charset="utf-8" href="/style.css" media="screen" rel="stylesheet" type="text/css" /></head><body><div class="main"><div class="header"><h1><a href="/">cheat sheets.</a></h1><code class="header">$ command line ruby cheat sheets</code></div></div><div class="content"><pre>For leela and fry to pair:
  hitch leela fry
To clear pair info:
  hitch -u
For a complete list of features:
  hitch -h
To print out the necessary shell function and aliases you need to add to your ~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc
  hitch --setup
Creating a Gravatar for your pair:
  Once I've hitched with my pair. (e.g. hitch leela fry) I have now created a unique email: dev+fry+leela@example.com
  Then, I go to gravatar.com. Add an image to that particular email address and I'm done.</pre></div><div class="clear"></div><div class="footer">Powered by <a href="http://www.sinatrarb.com/">Sinatra</a>,
